WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:23.825
Today we will learn about scion grafting. Grafting is when we join two plant parts together to make one strong plant. Why do we graft? We take a scion with the best fruit or flowers and join it to a rootstock with strong roots. Together they make a better plant. Step 1. Choose a healthy scion. This is a young branch with two or three buds.

00:00:24.345 --> 00:00:44.795
Cut the bottom at an angle using a sharp, clean knife. Step two, now cut the rootstock. Make the same angled cut on the top of the rootstock so it matches the scion. Step 3. Join the scion and rootstock together. Press the cut surfaces tightly. Make sure the green layers on both sides line up.

00:00:45.215 --> 00:01:04.515
This is called matching the cambium. Step four, wrap the graft tightly with grafting tape. This holds the pieces together and keeps them moist while they heal. After a few weeks, the graft heals and the two parts grow together as one plant. Well done, Caleb. Now you know how to do scion grafting.
